# zradar Cursor Rules

See [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and [CODING_GUIDELINES.md](CODING_GUIDELINES.md) for the full operating guide.

---

## Quick Rules

### Do
- Use `just` recipes for all lifecycle commands (build, test, fmt, lint, migrate)
- Write async I/O; never block the Tokio executor
- Enforce `org_id` + `project_id` filters on every data query
- Use `thiserror` for structured errors; add context on propagation
- Use newtypes for IDs (`OrganizationId`, `ProjectId`, `TraceId`, etc.)
- Keep Clippy warning-free; run `just lint` before finishing

### Don't
- Call `cargo`, `docker-compose`, or `sqlx` directly when a `just` recipe exists
- Hold locks across `.await` points
- Panic in library code — always return `Result`
- Hardcode secrets, tokens, API keys, or production endpoints
- Run `just clean-all` unless explicitly requested

---

## Architecture at a Glance

```
crates/applications/zradar-server   // OTLP gRPC + Admin HTTP (single binary)
crates/services/api                 // Admin HTTP routes
crates/services/api-optel           // OTLP gRPC + circuit breaker + rate limiter
crates/core/zradar-models           // Shared data structures
crates/core/zradar-traits           // Trait abstractions
crates/core/zradar-parquet          // Parquet writer/reader, compactor, file mover
crates/core/zradar-retention        // Retention policies + cleanup
crates/plugins/zradar-plugin-postgres // Postgres control plane repos
crates/plugins/zradar-plugin-s3     // S3 block storage backend
```

Storage split:
- **PostgreSQL** — control plane: file_list, stream_stats, settings, retention, audit
- **Parquet** — telemetry: traces, spans, metrics, logs

---

## Preferred Validation Sequence

```bash
just fmt
just check
just lint
just test
```
